sentences: Cornelia Herrmann (born in 1977) is an Austrian pianist.

In 1996, Herrmann was the youngest finalist and winner of the International Johann Sebastian Bach Competition in Leipzig and in 1999 she won the special prize of the Internationaler Mozartwettbewerb Salzburg.

In 2002, she made her debut at the Salzburg Festival and in 2003 conducted Mozart's recitative and rondo Ch'io mi scordi di te?

In May 2014, Herrmann started her own chamber music festival "Musiktage Hundsmarktmühle" at Lake Fuschlsee in Salzburg.
The chamber music concerts take place in the hayloft of the 16th century Hundsmarktmühle.
